WebDriver Locators

>Not as useful
Link text
TagName
XPath

>More Useful
ID
Class
Name
CSS selector - MOST POWERFUL

(SEARCH BY VALUE) - BEST PRACTICE
	HTML: <input id="q" class="q" name="q">

	ID
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector('#q'));

	CLASS
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector('.q'));

	NAME
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("input[name='q']"));

	HTML: <input class="q" type="text">

	TAG & CLASS
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("input.q"));

	TAG & ID
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("input#q"));

	TAG & ATTRIBUTE e.g. radio button: search by type  + value
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("input[type='radio']"));
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("input[value='radio button']"));

	HTML: 	<button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">
		<button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-success">
		<button type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-info">
	MULTIPLE CLASSES
	driver.findElement(By.cssSelector(".btn.btn-lg.btn-success']"));

(SEARCH BY WILDCARD) - 2nd BEST PRACTICE							HTML:<div id ="randomID_textField">
	EXACT MATCH
		a[id='id']			>>>>>>>>>			driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("div[id='textField']"));

	PREFIX ^
		a[id^='id_prefix_']		>>>>>>>>>			driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("div[id^='textField']"));

	SUFFIX $
		a[id$='_id_suffix']		>>>>>>>>>			driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("div[id$='textField']"));

	SUBSTRING *
		a[id*='id_pattern']		>>>>>>>>>			driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("div[id*='textField']"));


(SEARCH CHILD IN LIST) >>>>>>>>>driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("#list li:nth-child(n)"));


<ul id ="list">
	<li>One</li>
	<li>Two</li>
	<li>Three</li>
</ul>










